  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      An individual randomised controlled trial (RCT) to evaluate the effectiveness of a
      voice-based mobile phone health (mHealth) intervention to support post-abortion family
      planning (PAFP) at four Marie Stopes International clinics in Cambodia.

      The study seeks to address the research question: does a PAFP mHealth intervention increase
      use of contraception in Cambodia?
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
